      • queueDispatch

        EntityPacketContext queueDispatch(EntityPacket... packets)
        Queue a set of entity packets for sending after the event. Delays will be chained using the default delays for each packet type.
        Parameters:
        packets - the packets to queue
        Returns:
        This, to allow for chaining

      • queueDispatch

        EntityPacketContext queueDispatch(EntityPacket[] packets,
                                  int[] delays)
        Queue a set of entity packets for sending after the event. Delays for each packet will be taken from the array at the same index; however, if the delays array is not big enough, no delay will be used. If the delay given by the array is negative, no delay will be used.
        Parameters:
        packets - the packets to queue
        delays - the delays to use for these packets
        Returns:
        This, to allow for chaining

      • queueDispatch

        EntityPacketContext queueDispatch(EntityPacket[] packets,
                                  int delay)
        Queue a set of entity packets for sending after the event. No delays for any packets beside the first.
        Parameters:
        packets - the packets to queue
        delay - the delay to use before the first packet
        Returns:
        This, to allow for chaining

        EntityPacketContext queueDispatch(EntityPacket packet)

      • execute

        void execute()
        Send all of the queued packets.
        This should not be called by third-party plugins; calling it is handled by the API.
